ZH: 免疫系统是人体的一种重要系统。
EN: The immune system is an important system in the body.

ZH: 免疫系统可以保护我们免受细菌和病毒的侵害。
EN: The immune system can protect us from bacteria and viruses.

ZH: 免疫系统会产生抗体来对抗外来侵入的病原体。
EN: The immune system produces antibodies to fight against invading pathogens.

ZH: 免疫系统在感染或受伤时会自动启动。
EN: The immune system activates automatically during infection or injury.

ZH: 免疫系统可以分辨正常细胞和异常细胞，从而对抗癌症。
EN: The immune system can distinguish between normal cells and abnormal cells, thus fighting against cancer.

ZH: 免疫系统需要充足的营养来保持健康。
EN: The immune system needs adequate nutrition to stay healthy.

ZH: 免疫系统的功能会随着年龄增长而逐渐减弱。
EN: The immune system's function declines gradually with age.

ZH: 免疫系统可以通过接种疫苗来增强免疫力。
EN: The immune system can boost immunity through vaccination.

ZH: 免疫系统有时会误攻正常细胞，导致自身免疫性疾病。
EN: The immune system sometimes mistakenly attacks normal cells, leading to autoimmune diseases.

ZH: 免疫系统受到压力或疲劳时容易受到影响。
EN: The immune system is easily influenced by stress or fatigue.

ZH: 免疫系统的功能会受到环境污染的影响。
EN: The immune system's function is affected by environmental pollution.

ZH: 免疫系统在保护身体免受疾病方面扮演着关键角色。
EN: The immune system plays a crucial role in protecting the body from diseases.

ZH: 免疫系统不断与其他系统交互，以保持整体的健康。
EN: The immune system constantly interacts with other systems to maintain overall health.

ZH: 免疫系统会产生记忆细胞，以便下次快速对抗同一病原体。
EN: The immune system produces memory cells to quickly combat the same pathogen next time.

ZH: 免疫系统的平衡对于健康至关重要。
EN: The balance of the immune system is crucial for health.

ZH: 免疫系统的异常活跃可能会导致过敏反应。
EN: Abnormal activity of the immune system may lead to allergic reactions.

ZH: 免疫系统的效率取决于个体的遗传背景。
EN: The efficiency of the immune system depends on individual genetic background.

ZH: 免疫系统在身体受到侵害时会产生炎症反应。
EN: The immune system produces inflammation response when the body is under attack.

ZH: 免疫系统在遇到新病原体时会逐渐适应并产生应对措施。
EN: The immune system gradually adapts and develops countermeasures when encountering new pathogens.

ZH: 免疫系统的健康状况直接影响个体的免疫防御能力。
EN: The health of the immune system directly affects an individual's immune defense capability.
